header.gameNote: FIU TIP-OFF CLASSIC AT MIAMI FL

article.headline: Western Illinois 75, Radford 72
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Sammy Hunter hit a tying 3-pointer for Western Illinois leading his team to a 75-72 victory over Radford in overtime Friday, the first night of the Adidas FIU Tip-Off Classic. After entering the extra period tied at 63, Western Illinois (2-0) took a 70- 69 lead with 1:46 remaining on a layup by Louis Johnson, who finished the night with a team-high 17 points. A layup by Troy Okeson stretched the lead to three, and a David Jackson free throw with 14 seconds left put Western Illinois up four, 73-69. Western Illinois received 17 points from Jackson, who played all 40 minutes. Hunter and Jerryck Owens-Murrey each added 13. Radford's (0-4) Reggie McIntyre led all scorers with 21 points. The team got another 20 from Chris Oliver, 14 from Martell McDuffy and 10 from Amir Johnson. Western Illinois won the rebounding battle 40-30 and shot 51 percent from the floor, including 55 percent in the first half.
